description.narrative:
The Sustainable Island initiative aims to support the development of two Indonesian islands towards a green and low carbon pathway through the integration of effective solid waste management and waste-to-energy solutions. The Sustainable Island Initiative will:

-	Improve framework conditions related to sustainable development within waste management and energy; 
-	Operationalize already formulated strategies and targets by providing analyses and recommendations; 
-	Assist the process of implementing the regional policies and plans for waste management and energy; 
-	Move sustainable waste- and energy management past national plans towards actual implementation at a regional level.
